cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of finding good policies for POMDPs, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of search heuristics such as local search, simulated annealing, and genetic algorithms suggests a focus on optimization and search algorithms, which are also relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of finite-memory policies and the comparison to a dynamic programming algorithm suggest a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
